<specimenCount box="[151,225,494,519]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" type="generic">600 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="493" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,314,663]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,530,555]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was previously known exclusively from the 
<typeStatus box="[970,1018,531,555]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">type</typeStatus>
material collected along the coast of Cabo Frio, Rio de Janeiro (
<bibRefCitation author="Nucci" box="[475,718,566,591]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" refString="Nucci, P. R. &amp; Melo, G. A. S. de (2003) A new species of Pagurus (Decapoda: Anomura: Paguidae) from Brazil. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 83, 351 - 353. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315403007185 h" type="journal article" year="2003">
Nucci &amp; Melo 
<number box="[658,718,567,591]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), roughly near 
<geoCoordinate box="[899,1034,566,591]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" precision="15" value="-22.87889">
<number box="[899,930,566,591]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" value="22.0">22</number>
° 
<number box="[940,971,566,591]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" value="52.0">52</number>
’ 
<number box="[976,1008,566,591]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" value="44.0">44</number>
”S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1049,1194,567,591]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" precision="15" value="-42.01889">
<number box="[1049,1080,567,591]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" value="42.0">42</number>
°01’08”W
</geoCoordinate>
. The material herein reported expands the horizontal range of this species for about 
<number box="[868,883,603,627]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" value="2.0">2</number>
° of latitude to the north and 
<number box="[1214,1227,603,627]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" value="1.0">1</number>
° of latitude to the south of the 
<typeStatus box="[290,338,639,663]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">type</typeStatus>
locality, and also increases by 
<quantity box="[686,757,639,663]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
the lower depth limit at which this species is known to live.
</paragraph>
